summary: This document confirms the deregistration of the Gulfstream Aerospace G1159B aircraft with registration number N909JE from the United States Civil Aircraft Register, effective December 2, 2014. The last registered owner was Starbridge Landing Inc., and the aircraft is being exported to Venezuela.

connections.description: Oscar Alberto Faria Garcia is the President of Starbridge Landing Inc., the last registered owner of the aircraft.
Both are FAA officials involved in the aircraft registration process.

events.title: Deregistration of Aircraft N909JE
events.description: The aircraft was officially deregistered from the U.S. Civil Aircraft Register.

events.title: Request for Deregistration
events.description: Oscar Alberto Faria Garcia submitted a request for the deregistration of the aircraft.

events.title: Claim of Lien Filed
events.description: Hector Francisco Tosta filed a claim of lien against the aircraft, which was later returned as not recordable.

keyFacts: The aircraft N909JE was deregistered effective December 2, 2014.
The last registered owner of the aircraft was Starbridge Landing Inc.
The aircraft was exported to Venezuela.
A claim of lien against the aircraft was filed by Hector Francisco Tosta but was not recordable.
The deregistration was approved by Christine D. Mouncer.
